The paper deals with the algorithmic complexity of promise CSPs, which is a topic that falls under computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of linear programming and solving linear systems over rings suggests a connection to optimization (cs.DS) and algebra (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the connection between polymorphisms and algorithms, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
